# TestRail section - version from Shortcut

Before creating cases or sections, read the Shortcut story and **resolve version + product area**.

## 1. Read version signals (in order)

From `stories-get-by-id` (full):

| Signal | Field / source |
|--------|----------------|
| **Version (Scheduled Fix)** | custom field |
| **Version (Identified)** | custom field |
| **Milestone** | objective name |
| **Epic** | epic name (often includes version) |
| **Iteration** | iteration name |
| **User** | explicit version in chat |

Prefer **Version (Scheduled Fix)** when set, else milestone/epic/iteration.

**If version or product area is ambiguous → ask user** before picking section.

## 2. Product area → suite / section

Do **not** hardcode suite or section IDs in this rule.

Resolve from (in order):

1. `.cursor/qa-memory/project-context/current.md` (TestRail project/suite + section map)
2. Project prefs / knowledge (`pref` / `know`)
3. Live TestRail: `getSections` / `getSuites`
4. Ask the user

## 3. Version → child section

Pattern (team-specific details live in project-context):

- Parent bucket for the release (e.g. `26.3 … Improvement`)
- Child section named after the story theme
- Older / no bucket: story-named child under the product-area root

## 4. Before write

1. State in preview: **resolved version**, **chosen section path**, **section id** (existing or new).
2. `getCases` refs=story — no duplicates.
3. If no matching bucket → propose `addSection` parent + name, **ask** if unsure.

## 5. Example shape (IDs from your project-context)

Story · Milestone · Epic · Product area  
→ `{ProductRoot} / {VersionBucket} / {StoryTheme}` (new or existing child)
